Sentencas: Infiltrated La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3.delta (LSCF) sintered porous powder cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells have been investigated by synchrotron ultra-small angle x-ray scattering (USAXS).
Titulo: Synchrotron X-ray studies of model SOFC cathodes, part II: Porous powder cathodes

Sentencas: We demonstrated that atomic layer deposition (ALD) is the method for a uniform coating and liquid-phase infiltration for growing nanoscale particles on the porous LSCF surfaces.
Titulo: Synchrotron X-ray studies of model SOFC cathodes, part II: Porous powder cathodes

Sentencas: The MnO infiltrate, grown by ALD, forms a conformal layer with a uniform thickness throughout the pores evidenced by USAXS thickness fringes.
Titulo: Synchrotron X-ray studies of model SOFC cathodes, part II: Porous powder cathodes

Sentencas: The La0.6Sr0.4CoO3 (LSC) and La2Zr2O7 (LZO) infiltrates, grown by liquid-phase infiltration, were found to form nanoscale particles on the surfaces of LSCF particles resulting in increased surface areas.
Titulo: Synchrotron X-ray studies of model SOFC cathodes, part II: Porous powder cathodes

Sentencas: Impedance measurements suggest that the catalytic property of LSC infiltrate, not the increased surface area of LZO, is important for increasing oxygen reduction activities.
Titulo: Synchrotron X-ray studies of model SOFC cathodes, part II: Porous powder cathodes
